{"timestamp": "2026-05-21 17:21:40,692", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_0\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nDevelop a game that fuses Tetris and Bejeweled mechanics. \\nThis game needs to add keyboard control function.\\nFalling tetrominoes should lock into a grid and transform into colored gems. \\nThe game must support both Tetris line-clearing and Bejeweled match-3 clearing, triggering chain reactions and bonus points. \\nInclude a GUI (using a framework like Pygame) that displays the game grid, current score, and next tetromino preview, along with smooth animations. \\nNo sound effects are needed.\\n\\nOutput Format: python\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task1:\\n  Objective: Implement Tetromino mechanics: spawning, movement (left/right), rotation, gravity drop, and locking into the grid.\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Develop gem transformation logic: convert locked Tetromino cells into colored gems and detect match-3 patterns.\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Implement Tetris line-clearing mechanics: detect and remove full horizontal lines in the grid.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nDefine core data structures: grid representation, Tetromino shapes, gem types, and overall game state models.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"import enum\\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\\nfrom typing import List, Tuple, Dict, Optional\\n\\n# Constants\\nGRID_WIDTH = 10\\nGRID_HEIGHT = 20\\n\\nPosition = Tuple[int, int]\\n\\nclass GemType(enum.Enum):\\n    RED   = (255,   0,   0)\\n    GREEN = (  0, 255,   0)\\n    BLUE  = (  0,   0, 255)\\n    YELLOW= (255, 255,   0)\\n    PURPLE= (128,   0, 128)\\n    ORANGE= (255, 165,   0)\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass Gem:\\n    type: GemType\\n    position: Position\\n\\n# Tetromino definitions: each rotation is a list of (x,y) offsets\\nTETROMINO_SHAPES: Dict[str, List[List[Position]]] = {\\n    'I': [\\n        [(0,1),(1,1),(2,1),(3,1)],\\n        [(2,0),(2,1),(2,2),(2,3)],\\n        [(0,2),(1,2),(2,2),(3,2)],\\n        [(1,0),(1,1),(1,2),(1,3)]\\n    ],\\n    'O': [\\n        [(1,0),(2,0),(1,1),(2,1)]\\n    ],\\n    'T': [\\n        [(1,0),(0,1),(1,1),(2,1)],\\n        [(1,0),(1,1),(2,1),(1,2)],\\n        [(0,1),(1,1),(2,1),(1,2)],\\n        [(1,0),(0,1),(1,1),(1,2)]\\n    ],\\n    'S': [\\n        [(1,0),(2,0),(0,1),(1,1)],\\n        [(1,0),(1,1),(2,1),(2,2)],\\n        [(1,1),(2,1),(0,2),(1,2)],\\n        [(0,0),(0,1),(1,1),(1,2)]\\n    ],\\n    'Z': [\\n        [(0,0),(1,0),(1,1),(2,1)],\\n        [(2,0),(1,1),(2,1),(1,2)],\\n        [(0,1),(1,1),(1,2),(2,2)],\\n        [(1,0),(0,1),(1,1),(0,2)]\\n    ],\\n    'J': [\\n        [(0,0),(0,1),(1,1),(2,1)],\\n        [(1,0),(2,0),(1,1),(1,2)],\\n        [(0,1),(1,1),(2,1),(2,2)],\\n        [(1,0),(1,1),(0,2),(1,2)]\\n    ],\\n    'L': [\\n        [(2,0),(0,1),(1,1),(2,1)],\\n        [(1,0),(1,1),(1,2),(2,2)],\\n        [(0,1),(1,1),(2,1),(0,2)],\\n        [(0,0),(1,0),(1,1),(1,2)]\\n    ]\\n}\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass Tetromino:\\n    shape: str\\n    rotation: int = 0\\n    position: Position = (3, 0)  # starting x,y on grid\\n    color: Tuple[int,int,int] = field(init=False)\\n\\n    def __post_init__(self):\\n        color_map = {\\n            'I': (0, 240, 240),\\n            'O': (240, 240, 0),\\n            'T': (160, 0, 240),\\n            'S': (0, 240, 0),\\n            'Z': (240, 0, 0),\\n            'J': (0, 0, 240),\\n            'L': (240, 160, 0),\\n        }\\n        self.color = color_map[self.shape]\\n\\n    def blocks(self) -> List[Position]:\\n        offsets = TETROMINO_SHAPES[self.shape][self.rotation % len(TETROMINO_SHAPES[self.shape])]\\n        px, py = self.position\\n        return [(px + dx, py + dy) for dx, dy in offsets]\\n\\n    def rotate(self, direction: int = 1):\\n        count = len(TETROMINO_SHAPES[self.shape])\\n        self.rotation = (self.rotation + direction) % count\\n\\n    def move(self, dx: int, dy: int):\\n        x, y = self.position\\n        self.position = (x + dx, y + dy)\\n\\nclass Grid:\\n    def __init__(self, width: int = GRID_WIDTH, height: int = GRID_HEIGHT):\\n        self.width = width\\n        self.height = height\\n        self.cells: List[List[Optional[Gem]]] = [\\n            [None for _ in range(width)] for _ in range(height)\\n        ]\\n\\n    def inside(self, x: int, y: int) -> bool:\\n        return 0 <= x < self.width and 0 <= y < self.height\\n\\n    def is_empty(self, x: int, y: int) -> bool:\\n        return self.inside(x, y) and self.cells[y][x] is None\\n\\n    def place_gem(self, gem: Gem):\\n        x, y = gem.position\\n        if self.inside(x, y):\\n            self.cells[y][x] = gem\\n\\n    def clear_cell(self, x: int, y: int):\\n        if self.inside(x, y):\\n            self.cells[y][x] = None\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass GameState:\\n    grid: Grid = field(default_factory=Grid)\\n    current: Tetromino = field(default_factory=lambda: Tetromino(shape='I'))\\n    next_piece: Tetromino = field(default_factory=lambda: Tetromino(shape='O'))\\n    score: int = 0\\n    level: int = 1\\n    lines_cleared: int = 0\\n    gem_grid: List[List[Optional[Gem]]] = field(default_factory=list)\\n\\n    def __post_init__(self):\\n        self.gem_grid = [\\n            [None for _ in range(self.grid.width)] for _ in range(self.grid.height)\\n        ]\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-21T17:21:40.692757\"\n}"}
